More4Plus1.uk.title: Come Dine with Me
More4Plus1.uk.description: Edinburgh. The first host, 27-year-old interior designer and gentle giant James, plans to blow his guests' minds with his spicy Mexican menu. (Ep1/5)

More4Plus1.uk.title: Come Dine with Me
More4Plus1.uk.description: Edinburgh. Grandmother Katy plans an out-of-season 'Christmas tartan' evening, complete with costumes, games and a few revelations. (Ep2/5)

More4Plus1.uk.title: Come Dine with Me
More4Plus1.uk.description: Edinburgh. Glamorous solicitor Aisling hosts an Irish party. She has a piper on her doorstep, but Katy's not a fan of her main, and the guests all struggle with 'clean eating'. (Ep3/5)

More4Plus1.uk.title: Come Dine with Me
More4Plus1.uk.description: Edinburgh. American writer Harry serves up a menu inspired by his family, while Bruce breaks his own etiquette rules, and Aisling draws Bruce's portrait with razor-sharp hilarity. (Ep4/5)

More4Plus1.uk.title: Come Dine with Me
More4Plus1.uk.description: Edinburgh. Style-conscious Bruce hosts the final night. All week he's expressed a taste for the finer things in life. With expectations high, can he put his food where his mouth is? (Ep5/5)

More4Plus1.uk.title: Four in a Bed
More4Plus1.uk.description: The first visit is to The Bell House Hotel in Wiltshire, where owners Chris and Jacqui aim to bring London chic to the shires. But their absence at breakfast provokes criticism.

More4Plus1.uk.title: Four in a Bed
More4Plus1.uk.description: The second visit is to The Partridge in Oxfordshire, where Matthew Cockman and Paula Szkwarkowska share a passion for organic food. But the self-service breakfast has the guests up in arms.

More4Plus1.uk.title: Four in a Bed
More4Plus1.uk.description: The third visit is to Strawberry Gardens B&B in Heysham, where David and Susan Speak aim to make their guests feel at home with northern hospitality. But Paula sends back her evening meal.

More4Plus1.uk.title: Four in a Bed
More4Plus1.uk.description: The last visit is to The Bateman's Mill near Chesterfield, where Jade Hendon and Diana Yates aim to be the best, but David and Susan are quick to find hairs in the bathroom.

More4Plus1.uk.title: Four in a Bed
More4Plus1.uk.description: It's payment day, and fur flies as Jade tackles Matthew over feedback for The Bateman's Mill. The group thrash out their differences before the winner is revealed.

More4Plus1.uk.title: A Place in the Sun: Home or Away
More4Plus1.uk.description: Animal lovers Andrea and Stephen are looking for a bolthole in Bristol, as well as a main home in Estepona in Spain, that their children, grandchildren, four dogs and two cats can enjoy.

More4Plus1.uk.title: Car S.O.S
More4Plus1.uk.description: Jeep Grand Cherokee: Fuzz Townshend and Tim Shaw head for Somerset to turn former soldier Ben's run-down classic Jeep into an off-roading machine. (S11 Ep9)

More4Plus1.uk.title: Car S.O.S
More4Plus1.uk.description: Rover SD1: Fuzz Townshend and Tim Shaw travel back in time with a 1986 Rover SD1, which belongs to 58-year-old landscape gardener Darren, whose ill health has taken its toll. (S11 Ep8)

More4Plus1.uk.title: The Dog House
More4Plus1.uk.description: Champion Olympic cyclist Victoria Pendleton visits Wood Green, in search of a dog who she can co-parent with her mum. And lovebirds Shai and Orin meet Polo the lurcher. (S2 Ep8)

More4Plus1.uk.title: George Clarke's Building Home
More4Plus1.uk.description: Kazal and Eleena are ditching Dubai and moving back home to Solihull to be close to extended family. Can they overcome building blunders to create the ultimate hosting hub? (S1 Ep3/4)

More4Plus1.uk.title: 24 Hours in A&E
